# Linear Teams

Teams are the backbone of Linear's organizational model. Every issue belongs to exactly one team. Before creating issues, an agent must know the target team's ID.

## Listing Teams

```graphql
query Teams {
  teams {
    nodes {
      id
      name
      key
      description
      members {
        nodes {
          id
          name
          email
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

With the SDK:

```typescript
import { LinearClient } from "@linear/sdk";

const client = new LinearClient({ apiKey: process.env.LINEAR_API_KEY });

const teams = await client.teams();
for (const team of teams.nodes) {
  console.log(`${team.key}: ${team.name} (${team.id})`);
}
```

## Team Keys

Each team has a short key (e.g., `ENG`, `DES`, `OPS`) that prefixes issue identifiers. Issue `ENG-42` belongs to the team with key `ENG`. The key is immutable after creation.

## Workflow States

Each team defines its own workflow states. States have a `type` that determines their category:

| State Type | Meaning | Examples |
|------------|---------|----------|
| `backlog` | Not yet prioritized | Backlog, Triage |
| `unstarted` | Ready to work on | Todo, Ready |
| `started` | Actively being worked | In Progress, In Review |
| `completed` | Done | Done, Merged |
| `cancelled` | Won't do | Cancelled, Duplicate |

```graphql
query TeamWorkflowStates($teamId: String!) {
  team(id: $teamId) {
    states {
      nodes {
        id
        name
        type
        position
        color
      }
    }
  }
}
```

With the SDK:

```typescript
const team = await client.team("TEAM_ID");
const states = await team.states();

for (const state of states.nodes) {
  console.log(`${state.name} (${state.type}) — ${state.color}`);
}
```

## Cycles

Cycles are time-boxed sprints scoped to a single team. Teams configure cycle duration (typically 1-2 weeks) and auto-start behavior.

```graphql
query TeamCycles($teamId: String!) {
  team(id: $teamId) {
    cycles {
      nodes {
        id
        number
        name
        startsAt
        endsAt
        completedAt
      }
    }
    activeCycle {
      id
      number
      startsAt
      endsAt
    }
  }
}
```

## Team Labels

Labels can be workspace-wide or team-scoped. Query team-specific labels:

```graphql
query TeamLabels($teamId: String!) {
  team(id: $teamId) {
    labels {
      nodes {
        id
        name
        color
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Finding the Right Team

When an agent needs to create an issue but doesn't know the team:

1. List all teams and their descriptions
2. Match the issue's domain to the most relevant team
3. Use the team's `id` in the `issueCreate` mutation's `teamId` field

```typescript
// Find team by key
const teams = await client.teams({ filter: { key: { eq: "ENG" } } });
const engTeam = teams.nodes[0];
```

## Priority Levels

Priority is workspace-wide but assigned per issue within a team:

| Value | Label | Meaning |
|-------|-------|----------|
| 0 | No priority | Not prioritized |
| 1 | Urgent | Drop everything |
| 2 | High | Do soon |
| 3 | Medium | Normal priority |
| 4 | Low | When possible |
